protocol.comment: Searches the specified list for the specified object using the binary search algorithm. The list must be sorted into ascending order according to the specified comparator (as by the method_0 method_1 method), prior to making this call. If it is not sorted, the results are undefined. If there are elements in the list which compare as equal to the key, the choice of KeyPresentBehavior decides which index is returned. If no elements compare as equal to the key, the choice of KeyAbsentBehavior decides which index is returned. This method runs in method_2 time on random-access lists, which offer near-constant-time access to each list element.
